obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (128)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=128&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2 ***.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 25 of 1968, s. 3 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line
  line `3. 1st July, 1949, vide Notification No. I OA (4)/49, dated 1st June, 1949, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i)`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (129)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=129&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,—`
  line
  line `(a) “associate” means an associate member of the Institute;`
  line
  line `^1(aa) “Authority” means the Appellate Authority constituted under section 22A;`
  line
  line `(aaa) “Board” means the Quality Review Board constituted under section 28A;`
  line
  line `^2(ab) “Board of Discipline” means the Board of Discipline constituted under sub-section (1) of section 21A;`
  line
  line `(b) “chartered accountant” means a person who is a member of the Institute ^3***;`
  line ;
  line `^2(ba) “Coordination Committee” means the Coordination Committee constituted under section 9A;`
  line
  line `(bb) “Companies Act” means the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) or any other previous company law as defined in clause (67) of section 2 of the said Act;`
  line
  line `(c) “Council” means the Council of the Institute ^2constituted under section 9;`
  line
  line `^4(ca) “firm” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4 of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), and includes,—`
  line
  line `(i) the limited liability partnership as defined in clause (n) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009); or`
  line
  line `(ii) the sole proprietorship, registered with the Institute;`
  line
  line `^2(cb) “Director (Discipline)” means the Director (Discipline) referred to in section 21 and includes Joint Director (Discipline);`
  line
  line `(cc) “Disciplinary Committee” means the Disciplinary Committee constituted under sub-section (1) of section 21B;`
  line
  line `(cd) “Disciplinary Directorate” means the Disciplinary Directorate established under sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(ce) “fellow” means a fellow member of the Institute;]`
  line
  line `(d) “holder of a restricted certificate” means a person holding a permanent or temporary restricted certificate granted by a State Government under the Restricted Certificates Rules, 1932;`
  line
  line `(e) “Institute” means the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `^5(ea) “notification” means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the term “notify” shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `^1(eb) “partner” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4 of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), or in clause (q) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009), as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(ec) “partnership” means —`
  line
  line `(A) a partnership as defined in section 4 of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932); or`
  line
  line `(B) a limited liability partnership which has no company as its partner;]`
  line
  line `(f) “prescribed” means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^6[(g) “Register” means the Register of members of the Institute maintained under section 19 or the Register of firms of the Institute maintained under section 20B, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(h) “registered accountant” means any person who has been enrolled on the Register of Accountants maintained by the Central Government under the Auditor’s Certificates Rules, 1932;`
  line
  line `^1(ha) “specified” means specified by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `^4(haa) “sole proprietorship” means an individual who engages himself in the practice of accountancy or offers to perform services referred to in clauses (ii) to (iv) of sub-section (2);]`
  line
  line `^2[(haaa) “Standing Committee” means a Standing Committee constituted under sub-section (1) of section 17;]`
  line
  line `(hb) “Tribunal” means a Tribunal established under sub-section (1) of section 10B;]`
  line
  line `(i) “year” means the period commencing on the 1st day of April of any year and ending on the 31st day of March of the succeeding year.`
  line
  line `(2) A member of the Institute shall be deemed “to be in practice” when individually or in partnership with chartered accountants ^7[in practice ^8[or in partnership with members of such other recognised professions as may be prescribed]], he, in consideration of remuneration received or to be received—`
  line
  line `(i) engages himself in the practice of accountancy; or`
  line
  line `(ii) offers to perform or performs services involving the auditing or verification of financial transactions, books, accounts, or records or the preparation, verification or certification of financial accounting and related statements or holds himself out to the public as an accountant; or`
  line
  line `(iii) renders professional services or assistance in or about matters of principle or detail relating to accounting procedure or the recording, presentation or certification of financial facts or data; or`
  line
  line `(iv) renders such other services as, in the opinion of the Council, are or may be rendered by a chartered accountant ^7[in practice];`
  line
  line `and the words “to be in practice” with their ]grammatical variations and cognate expressions shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—An associate or a fellow of the Institute who is a salaried employee of a chartered accountant ^7[in practice] or ^9[a firm of such chartered accountants or firm consisting of one or more chartered accountants and members of any other professional body having prescribed qualifications] ^7[in practice] shall, notwithstanding such employment, be deemed to be in practice for the limited purpose of the ^10[training of articled assistants].`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 3 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. The words “and who is in practice” omitted by Act 15 of 1959, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 2012, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (ea) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 3, for clause (g) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 3 of 2012, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 3 of 2012, s. 2, for “a firm of such chartered accountants” (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 2, for “training of articled clerks” (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (130)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Incorporation of the Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=130&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) All persons whose names are entered in the Register at the commencement of this Act and all persons who may hereafter have their names entered in the Register under the provisions of this Act, so long as they continue to have their names borne on the said Register, are hereby constituted a body corporate by the name of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India, and all such persons shall be known as members of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Institute shall have perpetual succession and a common seal and shall have power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immoveable, and shall by its name sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (131)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Entry of names in the Register of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=131&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any of the following persons shall be entitled to have his name entered in the ^1[Register of members], namely,--`
  line
  line `(i) any person who is a registered accountant or a holder of a restricted certificate at the`
  line `commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person who has passed such examination and completed such training as may be`
  line `prescribed for members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(iii) any person who has passed the examination for the Government Diploma in Accountancy or an examination recognised as equivalent thereto by the rules for the award of the Government Diploma in Accountancy before the commencement of this Act, and who, although not duly qualified to be registered as an accountant under the Auditors' Certificates Rules, 1932, fulfils such conditions as the Central Government may specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(iv) any person who, at the commencement of this Act, is engaged in the practice of accountancy in any Part B State and who, although not possessing the requisite qualifications to be registered as an accountant under the Auditors' Certificates Rules, 1932, fulfils such conditions as the Central Government may specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `^2[(v) any person who has passed such other examination and completed such other training ^3[without India] as is recognised by the Central Government or the Council as being equivalent to the examination and training prescribed for members of the Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any person who is not permanently residing in India, the Central Government or the Council, as the case may be, may impose such further conditions as it may deem fit;]`
  line
  line `(vi) any person domiciled in India, who at the commencement of this Act is studying for any foreign examination and is at the same time undergoing training, whether within or without India, or,who, having passed such foreign examination, is at the commencement of this Act undergoing training, whether within or without India:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such examination or training was recognised before the commencement of this Act for the purpose of conferring the right to be registered as an accountant under the Auditors' Certificates Rules, 1932, and provided further that such person passes the examination or completes the training within five years after the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person belonging to the class mentioned in clause (i) of sub-section (1) shall have his name entered in the ^1[Register of members] without the payment of any entrance fee.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Every person belonging to any of the classes mentioned in clauses (ii), (iii), (iv), (v) and (vi) of sub-section (1) shall have his name entered in the Register on application being made and granted in the prescribed manner and on payment of such fees, as may be determined, by notification, by the Council ^5***:`
  line
  line ^6*****.]
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall take such steps as may be necessary for the purpose of having the names of all persons belonging to the class mentioned in clause (i) of sub-section (1) entered in the ^1[Register of members].`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 4, for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 40 of 1955, s. 2, for clause (v) (w.e.f. 21-10-1955).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 4, for "without India" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 3, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `5. The words ", which shall not exceed rupees three thousand" omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 4 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. The Proviso omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (132)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Fellows and Associates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=132&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The members of the Institute shall be divided into two classes designated respectively as associates and fellows.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person shall, on his name being entered in the ^1[Register of members], be deemed to have become an associate member of the Institute and be entitled to use the letters A. C. A. after his name to indicate that he is an associate member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) A member, being an associate who has been in continuous practice in India for at least five years, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, or whether partly before and partly after the commencement of this Act, and a member who has been an associate for a continuous period of not less than five years and who possesses such qualifications as the Council may prescribe with a view to ensuring that he has experience equivalent to the experience normally acquired as a result of continuous practice for a period of five years as a chartered accountant shall, on payment of such fees, as may be determined, by notification, by the Council ^3***, and on application made and granted in the prescribed manner, be entered in the Register as a fellow of the Institute and shall be entitled to use the letters F. C. A. after his name to indicate that he is a fellow of the Institute of Chartered Accountants:`
  line
  line ^4*****.]
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for “Register” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 4, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `3. The words “which shall not exceed rupees five thousand” omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 5 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. The Proviso omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (133)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Certificate of practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=133&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) No member of the Institute shall be entitled to practise ^1[whether in India or elsewhere] unless he has obtained from the Council a certificate of practice:`
  line
  line `^2[(2)Every such member shall pay annual fee for the certificate as may be determined, by notification,`
  line `by the Council, and such fee shall be payable on or before the 1st day of April each year:]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) The certificate of practice obtained under sub-section (1) may be cancelled by the Council under such circumstances as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 6, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 5 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (134)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Members to be known as Chartered Accountants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=134&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[Every member of the Institute in practice shall, and any other member may, use the designation of a chartered accountant and no member using such designation shall use any other description, whether in addition thereto or in substitution therefore]:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to prohibit any such person from adding any other description or letters to his name, if entitled thereto, to indicate membership of such other Institute of Accountancy, whether in India or elsewhere, as may be recognised in this behalf by the Council, or any other qualification that he may possess, or to prohibit a firm, all the partners of which are members of the Institute and in practice, from being known by its firm name as Chartered Accountants.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (135)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Disabilities.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=135&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 4, a person shall not be entitled to`
  line `have his name entered in or borne on the ^1[Register of members] if he--`
  line
  line `(i) has not attained the age of twenty-one years at the time of his application for the entry of his name in the ^1[Register of members]; or`
  line
  line `^2[(ii) is of unsound mind and stands so adjudged by a competent court; or]`
  line
  line `(iii) is an undischarged insolvent ^3[or an undischarged bankrupt]; or`
  line
  line `^3[(iiia) is declared bankrupt under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016); or]`
  line
  line `(iv) being a discharged insolvent, has not obtained from the Court a certificate stating that his`
  line `insolvency was caused by misfortune without any misconduct on his part; or`
  line
  line `(v) has been convicted by a competent Court, whether within or without India, of an offence`
  line `involving moral turpitude and punishable with ^4*** imprisonment or of an offence, not of a technical nature, committed by him in his professional capacity unless in respect of the offence committed he has either been granted a pardon or, on an application made by him in this behalf, the Central Government has, by an order in writing, removed the disability; or`
  line
  line `^5[(vi) has been removed from membership of the Institute on being found on inquiry to have been guilty of professional or other misconduct:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has been removed from membership for a specified period, shall not be entitled to have his name entered in the ^1[Register of members] until the expiry of such period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 7, for “Register” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 7 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. The words “transportation or” omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 7, for clause (vi) (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (136)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Constitution of the Council of the Institute`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=136&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Council of the Institute for the management of the affairs of the Institute and for discharging the functions assigned to it under this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The Council shall be composed of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) not more than thirty-two persons elected by the members of the Institute from amongst the fellows of the Institute chosen in such manner and from such regional constituencies as may be specified:`
  line
  line `Provided that a fellow of the Institute, who has been found guilty of any professional or other`
  line `misconduct and whose name is removed from the ^2[Register of members] or has been awarded penalty of fine, shall not be eligible to contest the election,--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of misconduct falling under the First Schedule of this Act, for a period of ^3[four years];`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of misconduct falling under the Second Schedule of this Act, for a period of ^4[eight years, ]`
  line
  line `from the completion of the period of removal of name from the ^2[Register of members] or payment of fine, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) not more than eight persons to be nominated in the specified manner, by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `^5[(3) No person holding a post under the Central Government or a State Government shall be eligible for election to the Council under clause (a) of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) No ^6[member of the Institute or any partner of a firm] who has been auditor of the Institute shall be eligible for election to the Council under clause (a) of sub-section (2), for a period of ^7[four years] after he ceases to be an auditor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 6, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 5-9-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 8, for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "three years" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "six years" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006,s. 6 (w.e.f. 5-9-2006).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for three years (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 8, for person (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (66835)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 10
  title `Coordination Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `!1. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 9 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=66835&sectionno=9A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) There shall be a Coordination Committee consisting of the`
  line `President, Vice-President and the Secretary of the Council of each of the Institutes of Chartered`
  line `Accountants of India, the Cost Accountants of India and the Company Secretaries of India for the`
  line `development and harmonisation of the professions of Chartered Accountants, Cost Accountants and`
  line `Company Secretaries.`
  line
  line `(2) The meeting of the Coordination Committee shall be chaired by the Secretary, Ministry of`
  line `Corporate Affairs.`
  line
  line `(3) The meeting of the Coordination Committee shall be held once in every quarter of a year.`
  line
  line `(4) The Committee shall be responsible for the effective coordination of the functions assigned to`
  line `each Institute and shall––`
  line
  line `(i) ensure quality improvement of the academics, infrastructure, research and all related works of`
  line `the Institute;`
  line
  line `(ii) focus on the coordination and collaboration among the professions, to make the profession`
  line `more effective and robust;`
  line
  line `(iii) align the cross-disciplinary regulatory mechanisms for inter professional development;`
  line
  line `(iv) make recommendations in matters relating to regulatory policies for the professions;`
  line
  line `(v) perform such other functions incidental to clauses (i) to (iv) above.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (137)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Re-election or re-nomination to Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=137&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Re-election or re-nomination to Council.-^2[1] A member of the Council, elected or nominated under sub-section (2) of section 9, shall be eligible for re-election or, as the case may be, re-nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that no member shall hold the office for more than ^3[ two consecutive terms]:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a member of the Council, who is or has been elected as President under sub-section (1) of section 12, shall not be eligible for election or nomination as a member of the Council.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a member of the Council who`
  line `immediately at the commencement of the Chartered Accountants, the Cost and Works Accountants and`
  line `the Company Secretaries (Amendment) Act, 2022, has held office as such member for two terms or is`
  line `holding office for the second term of three years, shall be eligible to contest for one more term of four`
  line `years and a member who has held office for one term or is holding office for the first term of three years,`
  line `shall be eligible to contest for two more consecutive terms.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid. for section 10 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Section 10 shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) by Act 12 of 2022, s. 10 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for three consecutive terms (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (138)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 12
  title `Settlement of dispute regarding election.`
  content `^1[10A. Settlement of dispute regarding election.-- In case of any dispute regarding any election under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 9, the aggrieved person may make an application within thirty days from the date of declaration of the result of election to the Secretary of the Institute, who shall forward the same to the Central Government.]`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=138&sectionno=10A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_10_b:
  sectionId (139)
  sectionNo 10B
  orderNo 13
  title `Establishment of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=139&sectionno=10B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[10B. Establishment of Tribunal.--(1) On receipt of any application under section 10A, the Central Government shall, by notification, establish a Tribunal consisting of a Presiding Officer and two other`
  line `Members to decide such dispute and the decision of such Tribunal shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment,--`
  line
  line `(a) as a Presiding Officer of the Tribunal unless he has been a member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a post in Grade I of the service for at least three years;`
  line
  line `(b) as a Member unless he has been a member of the Council for at least one full term and who is not a sitting member of the Council or who has not been a candidate in the election under dispute; or`
  line
  line `(c) as a Member unless he holds the post of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India or any other post under the Central Government carrying a scale of pay which is not less than that of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions of service of the Presiding Officer and Members of the Tribunal, their place of meetings and allowances shall be such as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) The expenses of the Tribunal shall be borne by the Council.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (140)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 14
  title `Nomination in default of election or nomination.`
  content `If any body of persons referred to in section 9 fails to elect any of the members of the Council which it is empowered under that section to elect, the Central Government may nominate a person duly qualified to fill the vacancy, and any person so nominated shall be deemed to be a member of the Council as if he had been duly elected.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=140&sectionno=11&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (141)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 15
  title `President and Vice-President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=141&sectionno=12&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council at its first meeting shall elect two of its members to be respectively the President and Vice President thereof, and so often as the office of the President or the Vice-President becomes vacant the Council shall choose another person to be the President or the Vice-President as the case may be:`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(2) The President shall be the ^2[Head] of the Council.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(2A) The President shall preside at the meetings of the Council.`
  line
  line `(2B) The President and the Vice-resident shall exercise such powers and perform such duties and`
  line `functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2C) It shall be the duty of the President to ensure that the decisions taken by the Council are`
  line implemented.
  line
  line `(2D) If, for any reason a vacancy occurs in the office of the President, or if the President is absent or`
  line `for any other reason, is unable to exercise the powers or perform the duties assigned to him, the Vice President shall act in his place and exercise the powers and perform the duties of the President.]`
  line
  line `(3) The President or the Vice-President shall hold office for a period of one year from the date on which he is chosen but so as not to extend beyond his term of office as, a member of the Council, and, subject to his being a member of the Council at the relevant time, he shall be eligible for re-election ^4[under sub-section (1)].`
  line
  line `(4) ^5[On the expiration of the duration of the Council, the ^6[President and the Vice-President] of the Council at the time of such expiration] shall continue to hold office and discharge such administrative and other duties as may be prescribed until such time as a new ^6[President and the Vice-President] shall have`
  line `been elected and shall have taken over ^7[charge of their duties].`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The Proviso omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 11 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for “Chief Executive Authority” (w.e.f.10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 11 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 9 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 10, for “On the Dissolution of the Council, the President of the Council at the time of such`
  line `dissolution (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 9, for President (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for charge of his duties (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (142)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Resignation of membership and casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=142&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member of the Council may at any time resign his membership by writing under his hand addressed to the President, and the seat of such member shall become vacant when such resignation is notified in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) A member of the Council shall be deemed to have vacated his seat if he is declared by the Council to have been absent without sufficient excuse from three consecutive meetings of the Council, ^1[or he has been found guilty of any professional or other misconduct and awarded penalty of fine,] or if his name is, for any cause, removed from the ^2[Register of members] under the provisions of section 20.`
  line
  line `(3) A casual vacancy in the Council shall be filled by fresh election from the constituency concerned or by nomination by the Central Government, as the case may be, and the person elected or nominated to fill the vacancy shall hold office until the dissolution of the Council:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that no election shall be held to fill a casual vacancy occurring within ^4[one year] prior to the date of the expiration of the duration of the Council, but such a vacancy may be filled by nomination by the Central Government after consultation with the President of the Council.]`
  line
  line `(4) No act done by the Council shall be called in question on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 12, for “Register” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 15 of 1959, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `4.Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 10, for six months (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (143)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Duration and dissolution of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=143&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The duration of any Council constituted under this Act shall be ^2[four years] from the date of its first meeting, on the expiry of which it shall stand dissolved and a new Council constituted in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Notwithstanding the expiration of the duration of a Council (hereinafter referred to as the former Council), the former Council shall continue to exercise its functions until a new Council is constituted in accordance with the provisions of this Act, and on such constitution, the former Council shall stand dissolved.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 14 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 15 of 1959, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 13, for “three years” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (144)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title `Functions of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=144&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Functions of Council.--(1) The Institute shall function under the overall control, guidance and supervision of the Council and the duty of carrying out the provisions of this Act shall be vested in the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, the duties of the Council shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) to approve academic courses and their contents;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) the prescribing of fees for the examination of candidates for enrolment;`
  line
  line `(c) the granting or refusal, of registration of a firm];`
  line
  line `(d) the prescribing of qualifications for entry in the ^3[Register of members];`
  line
  line `(e) the recognition of foreign qualifications and training for the purposes of enrolment;`
  line
  line `^4[(f) the prescribing of guidelines for grant or refusal of certificates of practice under this Act;`
  line
  line `(fa) to issue guidelines for the purpose of carrying out the objects of this Act;]`
  line
  line ^5****;
  line
  line `(h) the levy ^6*** of fees from members, examinees and other persons;`
  line
  line ^7****;
  line
  line `(j) the regulation and maintenance of the status and standard of professional qualifications of members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(k) the carrying out, by granting financial assistance to persons other than members of the`
  line `Council or in any other manner, of research in accountancy;`
  line
  line `^8[(l) to conduct investor education and awareness programmes;`
  line
  line `(la) to enter into any memorandum or arrangement with the prior approval of the Central`
  line `Government, with any agency of a foreign country, for the purpose of performing its functions under`
  line `this Act];`
  line
  line `(m) to enable functioning of the Director (Discipline), the Board of Discipline, the Disciplinary Committee and the Appellate Authority constituted under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) to enable functioning of the Quality Review Board;`
  line
  line `(o) consideration of the recommendations of the Quality Review Board made under clause (a) of section 28B and the details of action taken thereon in its annual report; and`
  line
  line `(p) to ensure the functioning of the Institute in accordance with the provisions of this Act and in performance of other statutory duties as may be entrusted to the Institute from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 11, for section 15 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 14, for clauses (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for clause (f) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (g) omitted by ibid., s. 14 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6.The words "and collection" omitted by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Clause (i) omitted by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for clause (l) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (145)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 19
  title `Imparting education by Universities and other bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 12 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=145&sectionno=15A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Imparting education by Universities and other bodies.--(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, any University established by law or any body affiliated to the Institute, may impart education on the subjects covered by the academic courses of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Universities or bodies referred to in sub-section (1) shall, while awarding degree, diploma or certificate or bestowing any designation, ensure that the award or designation do not resemble or is not identical to one awarded by the Institute.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall enable a University or a body to adopt a name or nomenclature which is in any way similar to that of the Institute.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (66685)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 20
  title `Functions of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 15 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=66685&sectionno=15B&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Functions of Institute.—The functions of the Institute shall include––`
  line
  line `(a) the examination of candidates for enrolment;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation of the engagement and training of articled and audit assistants;`
  line
  line `(c) the maintenance and publication of a Register of persons qualified to practice as chartered`
  line accountants;
  line
  line `(d) the maintenance and publication of Register of firms;`
  line
  line `(e) collection of fees from members, examinees and other persons;`
  line
  line `(f) subject to the orders of the appropriate authorities under this Act, the removal of names from`
  line `the Register of members and firms and the restoration of names to the Register of members and firms`
  line `which have been removed;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance of a library and publication of books and periodicals relating to accountancy`
  line `and allied subjects;`
  line
  line `(h) the conduct of elections to the Council of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(i) the granting or refusal of certificates of practice as per guidelines issued by the Council.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (146)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 21
  title `Officers and employees, salary, allowances, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=146&sectionno=16&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Officers and employees, salary, allowances, etc.--(1) For the efficient performance of its duties, the Council shall--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint a Secretary to perform such duties as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) appoint a Director (Discipline) to perform such functions as are assigned to him under this`
  line `Act and the rules and regulations framed thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may also--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint such other officers and employees as it considers necessary;`
  line
  line `(b) require and take from the Secretary or from any other officer or employee such security for the due performance of his duties, as the Council considers necessary;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) prescribe the manner of appointment, powers, duties and functions of the Secretary and other`
  line `officers and employees, their salaries, fees, allowances and other terms and conditions of service;]`
  line
  line `(d) with the previous sanction of the Central Government, fix the allowances of the President,`
  line `Vice-President and other members of the Council and members of its Committees.`
  line
  line `(3) The Secretary of the Council shall be entitled to participate in the meetings of the Council but shall not be entitled to vote thereat.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for section 16 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 16, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (147)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 22
  title `Committees of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=147&sectionno=17&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall constitute from amongst its members the following Standing Committees, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) an Executive Committee,`
  line
  line `(ii) an Examination Committee, and`
  line
  line `^1[(iii) a Finance Committee.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Council may also form such other committees from amongst its members as it consider necessary for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Act, and any Committee so formed may, with the sanction of the Council, co-opt such other members of the Institute not exceeding one-third of the members of the committee as it thinks fit, and any member so co-opted shall be entitled to exercise all the rights of a member of the committee`
  line
  line `(3) Each of the Standing Committees shall consist of the President and the Vice-President ex officio, and minimum of three and maximum of five members to be elected by the Council from amongst its members.]`
  line
  line `(4) The President and the Vice-President of the Council shall be the Chairman and Vice-Chairman respectively of each of the Standing Committees.`
  line
  line `(5) Every member of the Standing Committee other than the Chairman and the Vice-Chairman shall hold office for one year from the date of his election, but subject to being a member of the Council, he shall be eligible for re-election.`
  line
  line `(6) The Standing Committees shall exercise such functions and be subject to such conditions in the exercise thereof as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for clause (iii) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (148)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 23
  title `Finance of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=148&sectionno=18&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established a fund under the management and control of the Council into which shall be paid all monies received by the Council and out of which shall be met all expenses and liabilities properly incurred by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may invest any money for the time being standing to the credit of the fund in any Government security or in any other security approved by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The Council shall keep proper accounts of the fund distinguishing capital from revenue in the manner prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall prepare in the manner prescribed and approve, prior to the start of the financial year, an annual financial statement (the budget) indicating all its anticipated revenues as well as all proposed expenditures for the forthcoming year.`
  line
  line `^2[(5) The annual accounts of the Council shall be prepared in such manner as may be prescribed and`
  line `subject to audit by a firm of chartered accountants to be appointed annually by the Council from the panel`
  line `of auditors maintained by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that a firm shall not be eligible for appointment as an auditor under this sub-section, if any`
  line `of its partner is or has been a member of the Council during the last four years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the event it is brought to the notice of the Council that the accounts of the`
  line `Council do not represent a true and fair view of its finances, then, the Council may itself cause a special`
  line `audit to be conducted:`
  line
  line `Provided also that, if such information, that the accounts of the Council do not represent a true and`
  line `fair view of its finances, is sent to the Council by the Central Government, then, the Council may,`
  line `wherever appropriate cause a special audit or take such other action as it considers necessary and shall`
  line `furnish an action taken report thereon to the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^3[(5A) As soon as may be practicable at the end of each year, the Council shall circulate the audited accounts to its members at least fifteen days in advance and consider and approve these accounts in a special meeting convened for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(5B) The Council shall cause to be published in the Gazette of India not later than the 30th day of September of the year next following, a copy of the audited accounts and the Report of the Council for that year duly approved by the Council and copies of the said accounts and Report shall be forwarded to the Central Government and to all the members of the Institute.]`
  line
  line `(6) The Council may borrow from a scheduled bank, as defined in the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), or from the Central Government--`
  line
  line `(a) any money required for meeting its liabilities on capital account on the security of the fund or on the security of any other assets for the time being belonging to it, or`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of meeting current liabilities pending the receipt of income by way of`
  line `temporary loan or overdraft.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 15, for sub-sections (3), (4) and (5) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 17, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (149)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 24
  title `Register of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=149&sectionno=19&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Council shall maintain a Register of members of the Institute`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Register of members] shall include the following particulars about every member of the Institute,`
  line namely,--
  line
  line `(a) his full name, date of birth domicile, residential and professional addresses;`
  line
  line `(b) the date on which his name is entered in the ^2[Register of members];`
  line
  line `(c) his qualifications;`
  line
  line `^3[(ca) whether any actionable information or complaint is pending or any penalty has been`
  line `imposed against him under Chapter V, including details thereof, if any;]`
  line
  line `(d) whether he holds a certificate of practice; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other particulars which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) The council shall cause to be published in such manner as may be prescribed, a list of members of the Institute as on the 1st day of April of each year, and shall, if requested to do so by any such member, send to him a copy of such list ^5[on payment of such amount as may be prescribed].]`
  line
  line `^6[(4) Every member of the Institute shall, on his name being entered in the ^2[Register of members], pay such annual membership fee as may be determined, by notification, by the Council ^7***.`
  line
  line ^8****.]
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 18, for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s.18, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 17, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 16 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 16, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `7. The words , which shall not exceed rupees five thousand omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 18 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `8. The Proviso omitted by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (150)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 25
  title `Removal from the Register of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=150&sectionno=20&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Removal from the ^2[Register of members].--(1) The Council may remove from the ^2[Register of members] the name of any member of the Institute--`
  line
  line `(a) who is dead; or`
  line
  line `(b) from whom a request has been received to that effect, or`
  line
  line `(c) who has not paid any prescribed fee required to be paid by him; or`
  line
  line `(d) who is found to have been subject at the time when his name was entered in the ^2[Register of members], or who at any time thereafter has become subject, to any of the disabilities mentioned in section 8, or who for any other reason has ceased to be entitled to have his name borne on the Register.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall remove from the ^2[Register of members] the name of any member in respect of whom an order has been passed under this Act removing him from membership of the Institute.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) If the name of any member has been removed from the Register under clause (c) of sub-section (1), on receipt of an application, his name may be entered again in the Register on payment of the arrears of annual fee and entrance fee along with such additional fee, as may be determined, by notification, by the Council ^4***:`
  line
  line ^5*****.]
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 18, for section 20 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 19, for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 17 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `4. The words ", which shall not exceed rupees two thousand" omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 19 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line `5. The Proviso omitted by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (151)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 26
  title `Disciplinary Directorate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=151&sectionno=21&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[21. Disciplinary Directorate.--(1) The Council shall, by notification, establish a Disciplinary Directorate headed by an officer of the Institute designated as Director (Discipline) and such other employees for making investigations in respect of any information or complaint received by it.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of any information or complaint along with the prescribed fee, the Director (Discipline) shall arrive at a prima facie opinion on the occurrence of the alleged misconduct.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Director (Discipline) is of the opinion that a member is guilty of any rofessional or other misconduct mentioned in the First Schedule, he shall place the matter before the Board of Discipline and where the Director (Discipline) is of the opinion that a member is guilty of any professional or other misconduct mentioned in the Second Schedule or in both the Schedules, he shall place the matter before the Disciplinary Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) In order to make investigations under the provisions of this Act, the Disciplinary Directorate shall follow such procedure as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a complainant withdraws the complaint, the Director (Discipline) shall place such withdrawal before the Board of Discipline or, as the case may be, the Disciplinary Committee, and the said Board or Committee may, if it is of the view that the circumstances so warrant, permit the withdrawal at any stage.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 19, for CHAPTER V (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 18, for section 21 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (152)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 27
  title `Board of Discipline.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=152&sectionno=21A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[21A. Board of Discipline.--(1) The Council shall constitute a Board of Discipline consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) a person with experience in law and having knowledge of disciplinary matters and the`
  line `profession, to be its presiding officer;`
  line
  line `(b) two members one of whom shall be a member of the Council elected by the Council and the other member shall be nominated by the Central Government from amongst the persons of eminence having experience in the field of law, economics, business, finance or accountancy;`
  line
  line `(c) the Director (Discipline) shall function as the Secretary of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of Discipline shall follow summary disposal procedure in dealing with all cases before it.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Board of Discipline is of the opinion that a member is guilty of a professional or other misconduct mentioned in the First Schedule, it shall afford to the member an pportunity of being heard before making any order against him and may thereafter take any one or more of the following actions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) reprimand the member;`
  line
  line `(b) remove the name of the member from the Register up to a period of three months;`
  line
  line `(c) impose such fine as it may think fit, which may extend to rupees one lakh.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director (Discipline) shall submit before the Board of Discipline all information and`
  line `complaints where he is of the opinion that there is no prima facie case and the Board of Discipline may, if it agrees with the opinion of the Director (Discipline), close the matter or in case of disagreement, may advise the Director (Discipline) to further investigate the matter.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 19, for CHAPTER V (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 19 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_b:
  sectionId (153)
  sectionNo 21B
  orderNo 28
  title `Disciplinary Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=153&sectionno=21B&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[21B. Disciplinary Committee.--(1) The Council shall constitute a Disciplinary Committee consisting of the President or the Vice-President of the Council as the Presiding Officer and two members to be elected from amongst the members of the Council and two members to be nominated by the Central`
  line `Government from amongst the persons of eminence having experience in the field of law, conomics, business, finance or accountancy:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council may constitute more Disciplinary Committees as and when it considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The Disciplinary Committee, while considering the cases placed before it shall follow such`
  line `procedure as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Disciplinary Committee is of the opinion that a member is guilty of a professional or other misconduct mentioned in the Second Schedule or both the First Schedule and the Second Schedule, it shall afford to the member an opportunity of being heard before making any order against him and may thereafter take any one or more of the following actions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) reprimand the member;`
  line
  line `(b) remove the name of the member from the Register permanently or for such period, as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(c) impose such fine as it may think fit, which may extend to rupees five lakhs.`
  line
  line `(4) The allowances payable to the members nominated by the Central Government shall be such as may be specified.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 19, for CHAPTER V (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 19 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_c:
  sectionId (154)
  sectionNo 21C
  orderNo 29
  title `Authority, Disciplinary Committee, Board of Discipline and Director (Discipline) to have powers of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=154&sectionno=21C&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_21_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[21C. Authority, Disciplinary Committee, Board of Discipline and Director (Discipline) to have`
  line `powers of civil court.--For the purposes of an inquiry under the provisions of this Act, the Authority, the`
  line `Disciplinary Committee, Board of Discipline and the Director (Discipline) shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document; and`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit.`
  line
  line ^3*****.
obj_root_law_sections_21_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 19, for CHAPTER V (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 19 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `3. The Explanation omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 24 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_d:
  sectionId (155)
  sectionNo 21D
  orderNo 30
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=155&sectionno=21D&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_21_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[21D. Transitional provisions.--All complaints pending before the Council or any inquiry initiated`
  line `by the Disciplinary Committee or any reference or appeal made to a High Court prior to the`
  line `commencement of the Chartered Accountants (Amendment) Act, 2006 (9 of 2006), shall continue to be`
  line `governed by the provisions of this Act, as if this Act had not been amended by the Chartered Accountants`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2006.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 19, for CHAPTER V (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 19 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (156)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 31
  title `Professional or other misconduct defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=156&sectionno=22&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[22. Professional or other misconduct defined.--For the purposes of this Act, the expression`
  line `"professional or other misconduct" shall be deemed to include any act or omission provided in any of the`
  line `Schedules, but nothing in this section shall be construed to limit or abridge in any way the power`
  line `conferred or duty cast on the Director (Discipline) under sub-section (1) of section 21 to inquire into the`
  line `conduct of any member of the Institute under any other circumstances.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 19, for CHAPTER V (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 20, for section 22 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (157)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 32
  title `Constitution of Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=157&sectionno=22A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, constitute an Appellate Authority consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) a person who is or has been a judge of a High Court, to be its Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) two members to be appointed from amongst the persons who have been members of the`
  line `Council for at least one full term and who is not a sitting member of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) two members to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst persons having`
  line `knowledge and practical experience in the field of law, economics, business, finance or accountancy.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and other members shall be part-time members.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 19, for CHAPTER V (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 22 A (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_b:
  sectionId (158)
  sectionNo 22B
  orderNo 33
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and members of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 22 A (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=158&sectionno=22B&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[22B. Term of office of Chairperson and members of Authority.--(1) A person appointed as the`
  line `Chairperson shall hold office for a term of three years from the date on which he enters upon his office or`
  line `until he attains the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) A person appointed as a member shall hold office for a term of three years from the date on which`
  line `he enters upon his office or until he attains the age of sixty-two years, whichever is earlier.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_c:
  sectionId (159)
  sectionNo 22C
  orderNo 34
  title `Allowances and conditions of service of Chairperson and members of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 22 A (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=159&sectionno=22C&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[22C. Allowances and conditions of service of Chairperson and members of Authority.--The`
  line `allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the Chairperson and members and`
  line `the manner of meeting expenditure of the Authority by the Council and such other authorities shall be`
  line `such as may be specified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_d:
  sectionId (160)
  sectionNo 22D
  orderNo 35
  title `Procedure to be regulated by Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 22 A (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=160&sectionno=22D&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[22D. Procedure to be regulated by Authority.--(1) The office of the Authority shall be at Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(3) All orders and decisions of the Authority shall be authenticated by an officer duly authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_e:
  sectionId (161)
  sectionNo 22E
  orderNo 36
  title `Officers and other staff of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_e_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 22 A (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=161&sectionno=22E&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_22_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[22E. Officers and other staff of Authority.--(1) The Council shall make available to the Authority`
  line `such officers and other staff members as may be necessary for the efficient performance of the functions`
  line `of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other staff members of`
  line `the Authority shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_f:
  sectionId (162)
  sectionNo 22F
  orderNo 37
  title `Resignation and removal of Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_f_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 22 A (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=162&sectionno=22F&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_22_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[22F. Resignation and removal of Chairperson and members.--(1) The Chairperson or a member may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson or a member shall, unless he is permitted by the Central Government to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of term of office, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or a member shall not be removed from his office except by an order of the Central Government on the ground of proved misbehaviour or incapacity after an inquiry made by such person as the Central Government may appoint for this purpose in which the Chairperson or a member concerned has been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in respect of such charges.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_g:
  sectionId (163)
  sectionNo 22G
  orderNo 38
  title `Appeal to Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_g_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 22 A (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=163&sectionno=22G&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_22_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[22G. Appeal to Authority.--(1) Any member of the Institute aggrieved by any order of the Board of Discipline or the Disciplinary Committee imposing on him any of the penalties referred to in sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 21A and sub-section (3) of section 21B, may within ninety days from the date on which the order is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Director (Discipline) may also appeal against the decision of the Board of Discipline or the Disciplinary Committee to the Authority, if so authorised by the Council, within ninety days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Authority may entertain any such appeal after the expiry of the said period of ninety days, if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may, after calling for the records of any case, revise any order made by the Board of Discipline or the Disciplinary Committee under sub-section (3) of section 21A and sub-section (3) of section 21B and may--`
  line
  line `(a) confirm, modify or set aside the order;`
  line
  line `(b) impose any penalty or set aside, reduce, or enhance the penalty imposed by the order;`
  line
  line `(c) remit the case to the Board of Discipline or Disciplinary Committee for such further enquiry as the Authority considers proper in the circumstances of the case; or`
  line
  line `(d) pass such other order as the Authority thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall give an opportunity of being heard to the parties concerned before passing any order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (164)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 39
  title `Constitution and functions of Regional Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 20, for "The Council may constitute such Regional Councils" (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=164&sectionno=23&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[For the purpose of advising and assisting it on matters concerning its functions, the Council may constitute such Regional Councils] as and when it deems fit for one or more of the regional constituencies that may be specified by the Central Government under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 9.`
  line
  line `(2) The Regional Councils shall be constituted in such manner and exercise such functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (165)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 40
  title `Penalty for falsely claiming to be a member, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=165&sectionno=24&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(i) not being a member of the Institute,--`
  line
  line `(a) represents that he is a member of the Institute; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses the designation Chartered Accountant, or`
  line
  line `(ii) being a member of the Institute, but not having a certificate of practice, represents that he is in practice or practices as a chartered accountants,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable on first conviction with fine which may extend to ^1[one lakh rupees], and on any subsequent conviction with imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend to ^2[five lakh rupees], or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 28, for “one thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for “five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (166)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 41
  title `Penalty for using name of the Council, awarding degrees of chartered accountancy, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=166&sectionno=24A&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[24A. Penalty for using name of the Council, awarding degrees of chartered accountancy,`
  line `etc.--(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, no person shall--`
  line
  line `(i) use a name or a common seal which is identical with the name or the common seal of the`
  line `Institute or so nearly resembles it as to deceive or as is likely to deceive the public;`
  line
  line `(ii) award any degree, diploma or certificate or bestow any designation which indicates or`
  line `purports to indicate the position or attainment of any qualification or competence similar to that of a member of the Institute; or`
  line
  line `(iii) seek to regulate in any manner whatsoever the profession of chartered accountants.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person contravening the provisions of sub-section (1) shall, without prejudice to any other proceedings which may be taken against him, ^2[be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees, or with both on first conviction], and on any subsequent conviction with imprisonment which may extend to ^3[one year, or with fine which shall not be less than two lakh rupees but which may extend to ten lakh rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 29, for “be punishable with fine which may extend on first conviction to one thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for “six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees” (w.e.f.10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4 Omitted by Act 9 of 2006, s. 22 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (167)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 42
  title `Companies not to engage in accountancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=167&sectionno=25&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) No company, whether incorporated in India or elsewhere, shall practice as chartered accountants.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the company shall include any limited liability partnership which has company as its partner for the purposes of this section.]`
  line
  line `(2) If any company contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), then, without prejudice to any other`
  line `proceedings which may be taken against the company, every director, manager, secretary and any other`
  line `officer thereof who is knowingly a party to such contravention shall be punishable with fine`
  line `^2[which shall`
  line `not be less than two lakh rupees but] which may extend on first conviction to ^3[ten lakh rupees], and on`
  line `any subsequent conviction ^4[with fine which shall not be less than four lakh rupees but which may extend`
  line `to twenty lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2012, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 30 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "to five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (168)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 43
  title `Unqualified persons not to sign documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=168&sectionno=26&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than a member of the Institute shall sign any document on behalf of a ^1[chartered accountant in practice] or a ^2[firm of such chartered accountants] in his or its professional capacity.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall, without prejudice to any other proceedings, which may be taken against him, be punishable on first conviction with a fine not less than ^4[ one lakh rupees] but which may extend to ^5[five lakh rupees], and in the event of a second or subsequent conviction with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with fine not less ^6[two lakh rupees] but which may extend to ^7[ten lakh rupees] or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 22, for chartered accountant (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for firm of chartered accountants (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 23, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 31, for "five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "one lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "ten thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "two lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (169)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 44
  title `Maintenance of branch offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=169&sectionno=27&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a ^1[chartered accountant in practice] or a ^2[firm of`
  line `such chartered accountants] has more than one office in India, each one of such offices shall be in the separate charge of a member of the Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council may in suitable cases exempt any ^1[chartered accountant in practice] or a ^2[firm of such chartered accountants] from the operation of this sub-section`
  line
  line `(2) Every ^1[chartered accountant in practice] or a ^2[firm of such chartered accountants] maintaining more than one office shall send to the Council a list of offices and the persons in charge thereof and shall keep the Council informed of any changes in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 22, for "chartered accountant" (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for "firm of chartered accountants" (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (170)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 45
  title `Sanction to prosecute.`
  content `No person shall be prosecuted under this Act except on a complaint made by or under the order of the Council or of the Central Government.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=170&sectionno=28&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (171)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 46
  title `Establishment of Quality Review Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 24 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=171&sectionno=28A&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[28A. Establishment of Quality Review Board.--(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, constitute a Quality Review Board consisting of a Chairperson and ten other members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and members of the Board shall be appointed from amongst the persons of eminence having experience in the field of law, economics, business, finance or accountancy.`
  line
  line `(3) Five members of the Board shall be nominated by the Council and other five members shall be nominated by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b:
  sectionId (172)
  sectionNo 28B
  orderNo 47
  title `Functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=172&sectionno=28B&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[28B. Functions of Board.--The Board shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to make recommendations to the Council with regard to the quality of services provided by the members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) to review the quality of services provided by the members of the Institute including audit`
  line `services; and`
  line
  line `(c) to guide the members of the Institute to improve the quality of services and adherence to the various statutory and other regulatory requirements.]`
  line
  line `^2[(d) to forward cases of non-compliance with various statutory and regulatory requirements by`
  line `the members of the Institute or firms, noticed by it during the course of its reviews, to the`
  line `Disciplinary Directorate for its examination.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 24 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 32 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_c:
  sectionId (173)
  sectionNo 28C
  orderNo 48
  title `Procedure of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 24 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=173&sectionno=28C&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_28_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[28C. Procedure of Board.--The Board shall meet at such time and place and follow in its meetings`
  line `such procedure as may be specified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_d:
  sectionId (174)
  sectionNo 28D
  orderNo 49
  title `Terms and conditions of services of Chairperson and members of Board and its expenditure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 24 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=174&sectionno=28D&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_28_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[28D. Terms and conditions of services of Chairperson and members of Board and its`
  line `expenditure.--(1) The terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and the members of the Board,`
  line `and their allowances shall be such as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenditure of the Board shall be borne by the Council.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (175)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 50
  title Reciprocity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for Register (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=175&sectionno=29&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any country, specified by the Central Government in this behalf by`
  line `notification in the official Gazette, prevents persons of Indian domicile from becoming members of any`
  line `institution similar to the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India or from practicing the profession of`
  line `accountancy or subjects them to unfair discrimination in that country, no subject of any such country shall`
  line `be entitled to become a member of the Institute or practice the profession of accountancy in India.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Council may prescribe the conditions, if any, subject to which foreign qualifications relating to accountancy shall be recognised for the purposes of entry in the ^1[Register of members].`
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (176)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 51
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=176&sectionno=29A&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[29A. Power of Central Government to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of election and nomination in respect of members to the Council under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of service of the Presiding Officer and Members of the Tribunal, place of meetings and allowances to be paid to them under sub-section (3) of section 10B;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) t the form and fee for filing an information or a complaint under sub-section (1), the manner`
  line `of deciding a complaint or information as actionable or non-actionable under sub-section (2) and the`
  line `procedure of investigation under sub-section (7), of section 21;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure while considering the cases by the Board of Discipline under sub-section (2)`
  line `and time limit for payment of fine under sub-section (7), of section 21A;`
  line
  line `(da) the procedure while considering the cases by the Disciplinary Committee under sub-section`
  line `(2) and time limit for payment of fine under sub-section (7), of section 21B;]`
  line
  line `(e) the allowances and terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and members of the Authority and the manner of meeting expenditure by the Council under section 22C;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure to be followed by the Board in its meetings under section 28C; and`
  line
  line `(g) the terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and members of the Board under subsection (1) of section 28D.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 25 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 34, for clauses (c) and (d) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (49053)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=49053&sectionno=30&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, by notification in the Gazette of India, make`
  line `regulations for the purpose of carrying out the objects of this Act ^1***.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters:--`
  line
  line `(a) the standard and conduct of examinations under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the qualifications for the entry of the name of any person in the ^2[Register of members] as a member of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(c) the conditions under which any examination or training may be treated as equivalent to the`
  line `examination and training prescribed for members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions under which any foreign qualification may be recognised;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which applications for entry in the ^2[Register of members]`
  line `may be made;`
  line
  line `(f) the fees payable for membership of the Institute and the annual fees payable by associates and`
  line `fellows of the Institute in respect of their certificates;`
  line
  line ^3*****;
  line
  line `(h) the particulars to be entered in the ^2[Register of members];`
  line
  line ^4****;
  line
  line `^5[(j) the training of articled and audit ^6[assistants], the fixation of limits within which premia may`
  line `be charged from articled ^6[assistants] and the cancellation of articles and termination of audit service`
  line `for misconduct or for any other sufficient cause;]`
  line
  line `(k) the regulation and maintenance of the status and standard of professional qualifications of`
  line `members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(l) the carrying out of research in accountancy;`
  line
  line `(m) the maintenance of a library and publication of books and periodicals on accountancy;`
  line
  line `(n) the management of the property of the Council and the maintenance and audit of its accounts;`
  line
  line `(o) the summoning and holding of meetings of the Council, the times and places of such`
  line `meetings, the conduct of business thereat and the number of members necessary to form a quorum;`
  line
  line `(p) the powers, duties and functions of the President and the Vice-President of the Council;`
  line
  line `(q) the functions of the standing and other committees and the conditions subject to which such`
  line `functions shall be discharged;`
  line
  line `^7[(r) the qualification required for the purposes of sub-section (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(ra) the circumstances under which certificates of practice may be cancelled under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 6;`
  line
  line `(rb) the guidelines for granting or refusal of certificates of practice under clause (f) of sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(rc) the manner of appointment, powers, duties, functions, salaries, fees, allowances and other`
  line `terms and conditions of service of the Secretary and other officers and employees of the Council`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(rd) the manner of preparing annual financial statement under sub-section (4) and the annual`
  line `accounts under sub-section (5), of section 18;`
  line
  line `(re) the manner of maintaining a Register of members of the Institute under sub-section (1) and`
  line `the manner in which the annual list of members registered with the Institute shall be published under`
  line `sub-section (3), of section 19;`
  line
  line `(rf) the manner of making an application for grant of registration of a firm and the terms and`
  line `conditions of such registration under section 20A;`
  line
  line `(rg) the manner of maintenance of Register of firms, and other particulars including details of`
  line `pendency of any actionable information or complaint or imposition of penalty against the firm under`
  line `sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) and the manner in which the annual list of firms registered with`
  line `the Institute shall be published under sub-section (3), of section 20B;`
  line
  line `(rh) the manner of making available status of actionable information and complaints and orders`
  line `passed under sub-section (9) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(ri) the manner of preparing panel of persons under clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (1) and`
  line `the allowances payable to the Presiding Officers and members of the Boards of Discipline under subsection (8), of section 21A;`
  line
  line `(rj) the manner of preparing panel of persons under clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (1) and`
  line `the allowances payable to the Presiding Officers and members of the Disciplinary Committees under`
  line `sub-section (8), of section 21B;`
  line
  line `(rk) the salaries and allowances and conditions of service of officers and other staff of Authority`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 22E;`
  line
  line `(rl) the manner in which Regional Council may be constituted under sub-section (2) of section 23`
  line `and the functions thereof; and ]`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) All regulations made by the Council under this Act shall be subject to the condition of previous`
  line `publication and to the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) the Central Government may`
  line `frame the first regulations for the purpose mentioned in this section, and such regulations shall be deemed`
  line `to have been made by the Council, and shall remain in force from the date of the coming into force of this`
  line `Act, until they are amended, altered or revoked by the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and a copy of such regulations shall be sent to each member of the Institute`
  line `omitted by s. 26,`
  line `ibid. (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 35, for Register (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line `3.Clause (g) omitted by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line `4.Clause (i) omitted by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 23, for clause (j) (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 26, for clerks (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 35, for clause (r) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line `8. Omitted by Act 9 of 2006, s. 26 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (49054)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 53
  title `Powers of Central Government to direct regulations to be made or to make or amend regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=49054&sectionno=30A&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Powers of Central Government to direct regulations to be made or to make or amend`
  line `regulations.--(1) Where the Central Government considers it expedient so to do, it may, by order in`
  line `writing, direct the Council to make any regulations or to amend or revoke any regulations already made`
  line `within such period as it may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Council fails or neglects to comply with such order within the specified period, the Central`
  line `Government may make the regulations or amend or revoke the regulations made by the Council, as the`
  line `case may be, either in the form specified in the order or with such modifications thereof as the Central`
  line `Government thinks fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_b:
  sectionId (49055)
  sectionNo 30B
  orderNo 54
  title `Rules, regulations and notifications to be laid before Parliament`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 27, for section 30B (w.e.f. 8-8-2006)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=49055&sectionno=30B&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[30B. Rules, regulations and notifications to be laid before Parliament.--Every rule and every`
  line `regulation made and every notification issued under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made or issued, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule, regulation or notification, or both Houses agree that the rule,`
  line `regulation or notification should not be made or issued, the rule, regulation or notification, shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule, regulation or notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_c:
  sectionId (49056)
  sectionNo 30C
  orderNo 55
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_c_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 28 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=49056&sectionno=30C&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_30_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[30C. Power of Central Government to issue directions.--(1) In the event of non-compliance by the Council of any provisions of this Act, the Central Government may give to the Council such general or special directions as it considers necessary to ensure compliance and the Council shall, in the discharge`
  line `of its functions under this Act, comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in the opinion of the Central Government, the Council has persistently made default in giving effect to the directions issued under sub-section (1), it may, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the Council, by notification, dissolve the Council, where after a new Council shall be constituted in accordance with the provisions of this Act with effect from such date as may be decided by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall ensure constitution of a new Council in accordance with the provisions of this Act within a period of one year from the date of its dissolution.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Central Government has issued a notification under sub-section (2) dissolving the Council, it shall, pending the constitution of a new Council in accordance with the provisions of this Act, nominate any person or body of persons not exceeding five members to manage the affairs and discharge all or any of the functions of the Council under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_d:
  sectionId (49057)
  sectionNo 30D
  orderNo 56
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=49057&sectionno=30D&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_30_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^*30D. Protection of action taken in good faith.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or the Council or the Authority or the Disciplinary Committee or`
  line `the Tribunal or the Board or the Board of Discipline or the Disciplinary Directorate or any officer of that`
  line `Government, Council, Authority, Disciplinary Committee, Tribunal, Board, Board of Discipline or the`
  line `Disciplinary Directorate, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or`
  line `any rule, regulation, notification, direction or order made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 28 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `* Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_e:
  sectionId (49058)
  sectionNo 30E
  orderNo 57
  title `Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=49058&sectionno=30E&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_30_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[*30E. Members, etc., to be public servants.--The Chairperson, Presiding Officer, members and`
  line `other officers and employees of the Authority, Disciplinary Committee, Tribunal, Board, Board of`
  line `Discipline or the Disciplinary Directorate shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2006, s. 28 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `* Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (49059)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 58
  title `Construction of references.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 15 of 1959, s. 25, for section 31 (w.e.f. 1-7-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=49059&sectionno=31&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[31. Construction of references.--Any reference to a chartered accountant or a registered`
  line `accountant or a certified or qualified auditor in any other law or in any document whatsoever shall be`
  line `construed as a reference to a chartered accountant in practice within the meaning of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (49060)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 59
  title `Act not to affect right of accountants to practise as such in Part B States.`
  content `Nothing contained in this Act shall affect the right of any person who, at the commencement of this Act, is entitled to engage himself in the practice of accountancy in any Part B State under any law in force in that State, to continue to engage himself in the practice of accountancy in that State after the commencement of this Act.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353&sectionId=49060&sectionno=32&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00001_194938_1517807318353
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
